Biography

AS A BULLDOG:

2017: Reigned as UMD's rushing champion in his very first go-around with the Bulldogs ... amassed 706 yards and a team-leading eight touchdowns on the ground en route to securing a spot on the All-NSIC North Division second team ... averaged 5.2 yards per carry ... eclipsed the 100-yard run barrier twice, the last coming on a cold and blustering night in Bemidji, Minn. (a 17-0 UMD victory on Oct. 26) ... also caught 12 passes for 158 yards as a junior.

BEFORE UMD: Played two seasons at Fullerton (Calif.) College before enrolling at UMD in 2017 ... was a key contributor for a 2016 Hornet club that captured the programs's first California Community College Athletic Association title in 33 years ... rushed 13 times for 96 yards in the Hornets' Southern California Football Association championship win over Riverside College last November en route to being name Fullerton College's Player of the Game ... ranked second on the 2016 Hornet ground gaining charts with 480 yards on 73 carries ... finished with 224 yards as a first-year Hornet ... is a 2014 graduate of Bakersfield's Stockdale High School ... ran for an for 1,341 yards and 19 touchdowns as a senior with the Mustangs ... attained All-SWYL and All-BVarsity All-Area first team honors that season.

CAREER HIGHS: Rushing Attempts - 29 at Bemidji State (10/26/17). Rushing Yards - 128 vs. St. Cloud State. Rushing Touchdowns - 2 at Bemidji State (10/26/17). Longest Rush - 34 yds. vs. Minnesota Crookston (11/4/17). Pass Receptions - 3 vs. vs. Central Missouri (12/2/17). Pass Reception Yards - 41 at Mary (11/11/17). Longest Pass Reception - 21 yds. at Mary (11/11/17).
